HEADWORD: tat Major
<hw>⟦Eacute⟧`tat" Ma`jor"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧tat</ets> state + L. <ets>major</ets> greater.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The staff of an army, including all officers
above the rank of colonel, also, all adjutants, inspectors,
quartermasters, commissaries, engineers, ordnance officers, paymasters,
physicians, signal officers, judge advocates; also, the noncommissioned
assistants of the above officers.</def></p>

